items.title: Millions take holy dip as India's Maha Kumbh Mela begins
items.author: Reuters
items.content:
Nearly 15 million Hindus, six times the number expected, took a dip in freezing waters to seek absolution of their sins on Jan. 13, the first day of India's festival that could draw the world's largest single gathering of humanity.Â 
Â 
Held every 12 years, theÂ Maha Kumbh MelaÂ or Great Pitcher Festival, as the religious event in the city of Prayagraj in the northern state of Uttar Pradesh is called, attracts more than 400 million visitors, both Indians and tourists.
